<h1>Navbar</h1>

<p>The navbar component is used to render the main nav bar of your application.</p>

<h2>Usage</h2>

<p>The example below shows common usage of the nav bar with an embeded {{link-to "navigation list" "docs.layout"}}.</p>

{{#docs-demo as |demo|}}

  {{#demo.example name="navbar"}}

    {{#uxs-navbar title=title fixed=fixed as |bar|}}
      {{#bar.menu as |nav|}}
        {{nav.item "Home"}}
        {{nav.item "Account"}}
        {{nav.item "Logout"}}
      {{/bar.menu}}
    {{/uxs-navbar}}

  {{/demo.example}}

  {{demo.snippet "navbar.hbs"}}

{{/docs-demo}}


<h2>Properties</h2>

<p>Now explore the various properties available in this component:</p>

